    "Fricker distinguishes between testimonial and hermeneutical injustice.",
    "Testimonial injustice describes the discrediting of a speaker's words as a result of identity prejudice, e.g.",
    "as relating to ethnicity, gender, or religion.",
    "Through such devaluation, the speaker is prevented from contributing to the epistemic system (Dotson, 2014), i.e.",
    "transmitting their knowledge to others via testimony, and excluded from existing epistemic practices."
